BT 0 g /F2 22 Tf 174.0 670 Td (Sadness: It's Okay to Cry) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 11 Tf 121.20000000000002 635 Td (Sadness is a natural response to loss, disappointment, or when somethi) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 11 Tf 224.16 618 Td (ng doesn't go the way we hoped.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 13 Tf 72 570 Td (Mia's STORY:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 545 Td (Mia's best friend moved away last week. Everything felt gray. Food) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 525 Td (didn't taste good. Games weren't fun. 'I just feel so heavy,' Mia told) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 505 Td (the school counselor. 'That heaviness is sadness, and it's completely) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 485 Td (okay to feel it. Let me show you something that might help.') Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 13 Tf 72 445 Td (UNDERSTANDING THIS FEELING:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 420 Td (Sadness might feel like a heavy weight on your chest or a gray cloud over) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 400 Td (your head. You might want to be alone, cry, or not do your usual) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 380 Td (activities. Crying is actually GOOD for you - it releases stress chemicals) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 360 Td (from your body! Everyone feels sad sometimes. The key is knowing that) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 340 Td (sadness always passes eventually, like clouds moving across the sky.) Tj ET

